I heard penguins are aggressive. Aren't they the penguins...

33
00:01:24,235 --> 00:01:26,105
- whose droppings can fly 40cm?
- Yes.

34
00:01:26,975 --> 00:01:28,035
They can shoot their droppings.

35
00:01:29,175 --> 00:01:30,844
We're going to capture one now. Take a look.

36
00:01:30,845 --> 00:01:33,504
(They carefully approach the nest.)

37
00:01:33,505 --> 00:01:35,415
Grab the tail.

38
00:01:35,915 --> 00:01:37,585
It actually bites.

39
00:01:46,525 --> 00:01:49,255
Oh, my gosh. What's wrong with its belly?

40
00:01:51,695 --> 00:01:54,434
(It has no feathers on its belly.)

41
00:01:54,435 --> 00:01:55,794
It's used for incubating eggs.

42
00:01:55,795 --> 00:01:58,205
Do they have no feathers on the area where they incubate their eggs?

43
00:01:58,305 --> 00:01:59,305
Yes.

44
00:01:59,306 --> 00:02:00,475
(The brood patch is used to brood their chicks and eggs.)

45
